<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="23Jun1927"><font color="red">23 June 1927</font> <i>BLHW</i> (to Harriet Weaver): The dreadful cyclone in Holland drove me out &hellip; I arrived here the day before yesterday &hellip; Your guesses get nearer but <font face="wake">N</font> is the name of a &lsquo;place where&rsquo; not a &lsquo;thing which&rsquo; or a &lsquo;person who&rsquo;. You did not answer my question about Johannes Vermeer&apos;s View of Delft. I hope you got <i>transition</i> 4. There is such confusion here since I got back that I can&apos;t read it </div>
